1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Most bugs were inevitable before you typed.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:11,500
You enumerate the traps first.
The LLM never frames your risk list — anchoring defense.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:18,000
REAL / GHOST / NEW / UNRESOLVED
— each with a file:line citation.

4
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:25,000
REAL: confirmed by code.
GHOST: code disproves it.
NEW: model surfaced something you missed.

5
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:30,000
Decision: PROCEED_WITH_GUARDS.
1 high-severity REAL needs fix.

6
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:36,000
Lint re-verifies every citation against disk.
Out-of-range line numbers fail the build.

7
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:42,000
Citations the lint can't verify are not evidence
— no matter how confident the model sounds.

8
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:51,500
Four-level decision gate.
CI gates on the enum. Humans read the rationale.

9
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:00,000
pip install antemortem
Apache 2.0 · 111 tests · Anthropic / OpenAI / local
